# Command aspell

## What does this command do:

GNU Aspell a command line spell checker

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: `sudo dnf install aspell`
For Raspberry Pi install using: `sudo apt install aspell`
For Mac install using: `brew install aspell`

## Command path

For Fedora run: `aspell`
For Raspberry Pi run: `aspell`
For Mac run: `aspell`

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/GNUAspell/aspell

## Command options

# Interactively spellcheck a file (opens editor-like interface):
aspell check <file>

# Spellcheck a file in a specific mode:
aspell --mode=html check <file>
aspell --mode=tex check <file>
aspell --mode=markdown check <file>
aspell --mode=email check <file>

# Pipe mode (ispell-compatible): reads words and outputs corrections:
aspell pipe
echo "helo world" | aspell pipe

# List misspelled words from stdin:
echo "helo world" | aspell list

# Use a specific language/dictionary:
aspell -l en_GB check <file>
aspell -d en_US check <file>

# Ignore words shorter than N characters:
aspell -W 3 check <file>

# Ignore case when checking:
aspell --ignore-case check <file>

# Use a personal dictionary:
aspell -p ~/.aspell.en.pws check <file>

# List available dictionaries:
aspell dump dicts

# List available filter modes:
aspell dump modes

# Show current configuration:
aspell dump config

# Print version:
aspell -v

# Add a word to your personal dictionary:
echo "correctly spelled word" >> ~/.aspell.en.pws
